&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Staff Nurse - Early Pregnancy Unit&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Early Pregnancy unit at St.Peters Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We would like you to join our fast paced, dynamic and friendly team. We are looking for a Band 5 nurse who is enthusiastic and passionate about womens health and early pregnancy, who has the ability to work under pressure in a busy clinic. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must be an excellent communicator, with a willingness to develop new skills. Prior experience in womens health would be preferable but not a necessity as all training will be provided. If you are passionate about nursing, womens health and pregnancy then please get in touch. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; For further information please contact Sister Natasha Carrington James or Kaylee Shevill, Abbey Wing ext 6846/2662&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;natasha.carringtonjames@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;kaylee.shevill@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
